node.text:
has allowed me to deal with the negative shit in my life⁣
⁣
It was always there and it was always consistent  even when at times my life felt like it was falling apart. The crazy part is tho...it wasn’t always about the weight and the training itself only..it was about the community. The friends that I made while I was at the gym, the lessons I learned, the people who helped me throughout some of the roughest times in my life..this is what I am missing the most right now about the gym...⁣
⁣
With everything happening around the world today I was forced to close my gym @zooculture and I can’t wait to open it again to all of its members as well as the rest of you guys. I opened this gym 3 years ago on may 27th and it changed my life. The amazing people I’ve met, the huge life lessons I’ve learned, the incredible employees. The list goes on..⁣
⁣
I am writing this post today to tell you..Even tho the world is a bit crazy right now..everything is closed. Don’t let it stop you from being there for the people around u, even if it has to be on a FaceTime or a phone call. Take the time to reach out to the loved ones in your life and support them. We are all in this together.⁣
⁣
I love you guys. 
______
🎥: @jonbrandoncruz 🏋️: @zooculture

node.text:
My father hung himself when I was 6 years old..I spent most of my child-hood/young adult life searching for father figures. I realized that although it would never be the same I would be able to find my own inspiration and guidance in other father like figures throughout my life..

Although I grew up without a father..at this point in my life 26 years later I wouldn’t have changed a single thing, this had to happen…

Now take that back to when I was 12 years old..shit even up to 25 years old I struggled greatly with finding a “reason” as to why did this happen to me…why is this my reality and why don’t I have what other kids around me had..I would be filled with anger, resentment, depression, anxiety…the crazy thing about all of this is that eventually it started to make sense.

Why am I telling you guys this?? Because sometimes the things that can make us the best versions of ourselves are the things that can hurt us the most. The easier thing to do is to allow our circumstances to determine our success or our movements..but it really is in our own hands. NO MATTER WHAT. We have the power to make the things we want happen in this life. 

Let me put this into perspective…if I grew up with a father I know for a fact my life would be different today..I know for a fact all of those years in the gym would have hit differently…I used so much emotional energy to drive me throughout my years..still to this day it drives me. Now could I have let this emotional energy instead turn me down a darker path..of course…but this is ultimately YOUR CHOICE..just as it was mine.

I also know that if I grew up with a father all of the content I’ve made over the years speaking about my trials..speaking about my life wouldn’t have been the same. I was able to use the one of the darkest moment of my life to create light for others. I am beyond grateful and blessed to be here today to be an example of no matter what you go through in this life, you can come out on top and grow into the best version of yourself.

Remember this…there’s nothing in this world that we cannot overcome..except death..and if you are reading this..well then you ain’t dead, get your ass to work!
